column3: Pedro Cota is a video producer for NASA en español the agency's Science Mission Directorate.

column1: Hubble Images Colorful Planetary Nebula Ringed by Hazy Halo
column3: The colorful planetary nebula, NGC 2438, formed after the death of a Sun-like star. It appears to lie on the outskirts of the open star cluster, M46 (NGC 2437), when in fact it is in the foreground between us and the star cluster.

column1: Spotted by Hubble: Dark Star-Hatching frEGGs
column3: This image shows knots of cold, dense interstellar gas where new stars are forming. These Free-floating Evaporating Gaseous Globules (frEGGs) are located in the Northern Coalsack Nebula in the direction of Cygnus, the Swan.

column1: Crew Dragon Endeavour Recovered After a Successful Splashdown

column1: Mocha Swirls in Jupiter’s Turbulent Atmosphere

column1: Crew-3 Launches to the Space Station

column1: Observing Earth from the Space Station

column1: Hubble Spies Newly Forming Star Incubating in IC 2631

column1: Suits at the Ready for Next Spacewalk
